04/09/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu condemned recent acts of violence in Macedonia during a phone conversation Wednesday (3 September) with his Macedonian counterpart, Boris Trajkovski.
Moisiu also called for better implementation of the Ohrid Framework Agreement.
Along those lines, Fatmir Mediu, chairman of parliament's integration commission, blamed the violence on poor execution of certain Ohrid clauses.
He urged ethnic Albanians in Macedonia not to in engage in extremist activities.
The Macedonian Army arrived in Kumanovo earlier this week after several acts by the rebel Albanian National Army.
(Albanian Daily News, ATA, BBC - 03/09/03)
